    "text": "Men's Tennis / December 8, 2022\nMEN'S TENNIS ANNOUNCES 2023 SCHEDULE\nWomen's Tennis / December 7, 2022\nWOMEN'S TENNIS UNVEILS 2023 SCHEDULE\nMen's Soccer / December 7, 2022\nSARKOS NAMED TO UNITED SOCCER COACHES ALL-REGION SECOND TEAM\nPlay Video\nFeatures / December 7, 2022\nLEHIGH SPORTS CENTRAL: WOMEN'S TRACK AND FIELD\nMORE STORIES\nLEHIGH CALENDAR\nEVENTS\nRESULTS\nMEN'S BASKETBALL\n12.15 / 7:00 PM\nat Wisconsin\nMadison, Wis.\nMEN'S BASKETBALL\n12.17 / 7:00 PM\nvs St. Elizabeth\nBethlehem, Pa.\nWOMEN'S BASKETBALL\n12.18 / 2:00 PM\nvs Delaware\nBethlehem, Pa.\nPrevious\nNext\n1\n2\n3\n4\nPrevious\nNext\n1\n2\n3\nLEHIGH MEDIA WALL\n@LehighAthletics\nThe honors just keep on rolling in for Lehigh Men's’s Jack Sarkos. Sarkos was named to the United Soccer Coaches All-Region Team! 👏⚽️ 🔗: bit.ly/3VKgKvR\n@LehighSports\nThe honors just keep on rolling in for @LehighMSoccer’s Jack Sarkos. Sarkos was named to the United Soccer Coaches All-Region Team! 👏⚽️ 🔗: https://t.co/Bs6B6M5VOU https://t.co/eCECnVEL5R\n@lehigh_sports\n#TitleIXatLehigh led Lehigh Swimming and Diving alumna Sue Schlicht Marck to hold a Jacobs Pool record and be awarded the Karen A. Adam’s Award during her Lehigh career. Today, Sue is serving as District Sales Manager at OFS Brands!\n@LehighSports\n.@LehighTFXC Women's Track & Field head coach Khayla Atte and assistant coach Brooke Astor discuss the team's performance at the Fast Times Before Finals meet on Lehigh Sports Central presented by Lehigh Valley Orthopedic Institute, part of @LVHN https://t.co/Jpu3TMV25h\nLOAD MORE\nLEARN.GROW.LEAD.\nPrevious\nNext\n1\n2\n3\nPrevious\nPause\nNext\nCOPYRIGHT © 2022 LEHIGH UNIVERSITY ATHLETICS\nAll rights reserved.\nTerms of Service\nPrivacy Policy\nLearfield, opens a new window\nSidearm Sports Learfield, opens a new window",
